<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SOC-SOCCOL-COLUMN-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
U.S. OLYMPIC MEN'S TEAM SEARCHES FOR GOLDEN GOALS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 c.2000 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   So the Sydney Olympics will be about soccer stars Mia Hamm,
Brandi Chastain, Julie Foudy and the rest of the bunch that
captured the Women's World Cup last summer and the 1996 Olympic
Gold medal in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   NBC has made the U.S. women's team a focal point of its summer
marketing campaign and fall schedule, but what about men's soccer?
There will be a U.S. men's soccer team in Sydney and the men dream
just as big.
</P>
<P>
   In his wildest fantasy, Galaxy midfielder Peter Vagenas will
return from the Olympics sport ing a shiny gold medal and a small
request for Jay Leno, who undoubtedly will leave a number of phone
messages for the Pasadena resident to visit the ``Tonight Show.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I should probably start setting it up now, don't you think?''
joked Vagenas, expected to be named a starter for the U.S. Under-23
Olympic Team along with Galaxy teammates Danny Califf and Sasha
Victorine when the roster is unveiled on Aug. 15. ``Maybe I'll call
Jay and say, `Jay, if we win the gold medal, can I be on with Elle
McPherson? Think that's asking too much?' ''
</P>
<P>
   Not at all.
</P>
<P>
   But asking the men to win a gold medal in soccer? That would
draw more laughs than Leno's monologue.
</P>
<P>
   ``There is no pressure on us, everyone will be focused on our
women because they're the defending Olympic and World champions,''
said Califf. ``And realistically, our chances aren't that great.''
</P>
<P>
   The U.S. opens group play against the Czech Republic Sept. 13,
followed by games against Cameroon and Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
   All the U.S. team needs to do is finish in the top two in group
play to reach the single-elimination quarterfinals. But for those
keeping score, the U.S. has never escaped group play in the
Olympics. In fact, from 1924 to 1996, the U.S. team has a combined
4-12-6 mark.
</P>
<P>
   ``No one is saying it will be easy, but if we can get to the
second round (quarterfinals), who knows?'' said Califf. ``We could
get a good draw or pull off an upset and all of a sudden we would
be in the semifinals serving notice around the country.''
</P>
<P>
   Winning it all, of course, would be just as remarkable as the
1980 U.S. hockey team cap turing the gold in Lake Placid.
</P>
<P>
   ``It would be an unbelievable story and a great opportunity for
the young players like myself to leave a mark,'' said Califf. ``But
that's just dreaming, we have three games to play first.''
</P>
<P>
   On paper, the U.S. has virtually no chance of winning the gold,
but being in a group with Cameroon and Kuwait gives the Americans a
chance to reach the quarterfinals for the first time in history.
</P>
<P>
   ``We realize that, but we're not going over there to reach the
second round,'' said Vagenas. ``We want a medal; anything less
would be a huge disappointment.''
</P>
<P>
   Coach Clive Charles will name the 18-man roster for the Olympics
next week. Victorine said there is plenty riding on the final
decision.
</P>
<P>
   ``If we do well in the Olympics, this changes a lot of our
careers because we will be seen overseas,'' said Victorine. ``It
also changes our lives here. The Olympics will make us bigger
personalities. That's what the Olympics can do for you.''
</P>
<P>
   More than anything, though, it's a chance for men's soccer to
erase the memories of the 1998 World Cup in France. The U.S. team
finished last among the 32 teams.
</P>
<P>
   ``U.S. Soccer has said it hopes to make a big impact on the
world stage in the next 10 to 15 years,'' said Victorine. ``This is
our first big stage during that span. We're capable of making
noise, we just have to go out and do it.''
</P>
<P>
   Major League Soccer teams have turned the U.S. Open Cup into a
possible preview of the MLS Championship.
</P>
<P>
   Last year the A-League's Rochester Rhinos beat Colorado to
capture America's oldest soccer championship. This year, however,
all eight quarterfinal teams hail from MLS.
</P>
<P>
   All eight play tonight, with the Galaxy hosting the San Jose
Earthquakes at Cal State Fullerton at 7:30.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
