<P>
   OLY-SWIMSUITS (Indianapolis) _ When the Olympic trials begin on
Wednesday, American swimmers will make as much news for what they
are wearing as for what records they set in preparation for the
2000 Summer Games next month in Sydney, Australia. A bodysuit that
fits athletes from neck to toe has revolutionized the sport. At
least 10 world records have been set worldwide this year in the new
swim suits. Speedo's version is called the Fastskin suit, which
contains tiny, v-shaped ridges that allow water to pass over the
swimmer more efficiently. The super-stretch fabric also compresses
a swimmer's muscles, therefore reducing the buildup of lactic acid
that causes fatigue. By Jere Longman.
