<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ Pastors Dorothy E. Johnson, Ramona Hunter and
Emma Curtis-White lead congregations within blocks of each other in
Dayton, Ohio. Only Johnson was ordained in the Southern Baptist
Church, but all three are troubled by the Southern Baptist
Convention's declaration this summer that women should no longer
serve as pastors. They all know what it's like to be told, ``I
can't come to your church because you are a woman.'' (McCarty,
Dayton Daily News). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ If Bush picked Dick Cheney to buy some foreign
policy experience and gravitas, Gore apparently picked Lieberman to
buy some morality and integrity. The poll numbers show that it has
worked. (Nethaway, Waco Tribune-Herald). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KELSO- COLUMN _ Time magazine's Aug. 7 Republican Convention
issue contains a full-page cartoon map on Page 100 called ``A Map
of the Governor's Austin,'' done by artist Eric Chase Anderson. It
may be ``A Map of the Governor's Austin,'' but it's not the same
Austin I live in. (Kelso, Austin American-Statesman). MOVED.
</P>
