<P>
   FOOD-WATER _ When it comes to basic ingredients, it's hard to
get more basic than water. During this drought-stricken;
heat-ridden month of August we take a look at this liquid of life.
Cover: copy block with three teases to inside package. Inside: A
lengthy intro on recipe page to the roles water plays in cooking
and then a package on bottled water that looks at the craze and
offers the results of our taste test. (Walker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH COLOR PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BOTTLED-H2O _ They've become as important accessory to our lives
as cell phones. And before you can even contemplate the wine list,
you have to make a choice between still or bubbles, Fiji or France.
Bottled water is hip and getting hipper. It's the fastest growing
segment of the beverage industry and no matter if the water comes
from a protected spring or is purified tap water, consumers are
drinking it up. (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
