<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RECIPES-BUNDY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A RECIPE SITE, AND A&AMP;W TASTES, TO ROOT FOR
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 By BEVERLY BUNDY 
 c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Perusing the Internet the other day, I came across a terrific
recipe site.
</P>
<P>
   It's called www.KitchenLink.com, and it's a great place for
cooks looking for recipes, food news, hunger relief agencies, and
even specialty diet information and recipes. (I discovered the site
when looking for gluten-free recipes for a reader.)
</P>
<P>
   Another solid link on the site is for copy-cat recipes from
restaurants nationwide. Some are from the restaurants themselves;
others have been concocted by home cooks trying to duplicate a
dish.
</P>
<P>
   The first two chili dog recipes were posted by people who said
they knew someone who worked at A&AMP;W years ago, and that's how they
got the recipe. I'm sure that nowadays, the sauce for these dogs is
made at a central factory and shipped to the stores. But if you'd
like to try these at home, here are some decent versions.
</P>
<P>
   Also on the site, I found the recipe for the popular
strawberries Romanoff served at La Madeleine. This recipe came from
a chef at one of the Washington, D.C., outlets of the cafe.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   A&AMP;W CHILI DOG SAUCE
</P>
<P>
   Yields 20 cups
</P>
<P>
   2 cups finely chopped onion
</P>
<P>
   3 pounds ground beef
</P>
<P>
   1 cup vinegar
</P>
<P>
   2 cups sugar
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons salt
</P>
<P>
   4 tablespoons celery seed
</P>
<P>
   106-ounce can tomato puree
</P>
<P>
   4 tablespoons chili powder
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon pepper
</P>
<P>
   Saute onion and brown the hamburger. Add remaining ingredients
and simmer, stirring often, until desired consistency. (The
simmering step can also be done in a crock pot on low.)
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per cup: 297 calories, 10 grams fat, 38
grams carbohydrates, 17 grams protein, 52 milligrams cholesterol,
803 milligrams sodium, 29 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   A&AMP;W CONEY ISLAND SAUCE
</P>
<P>
   Yields about 25 cups
</P>
<P>
   5 pounds hamburger
</P>
<P>
   2 small onions, finely chopped
</P>
<P>
   64-ounce can Hunt's tomato paste
</P>
<P>
   64-ounce can tomato puree
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup cider vinegar
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons chili powder
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon pepper
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon celery seed
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   Brown hamburger and onions in very large skillet; drain. Add
remaining ingredients and simmer for 3 1/2 hours. Stir frequently,
as it will tend to stick. This freezes well.
</P>
<P>
   Author's note: To get that authentic taste, use only Kogel
franks and rehydrate dry minced onions in boiling water.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per cup: 334 calories, 13 grams fat, 34
grams carbohydrates, 23 grams protein, 69 milligrams cholesterol,
1,602 milligrams sodium, 35 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   A&AMP;W CHILI DOG SAUCE
</P>
<P>
   Yields 12 cups
</P>
<P>
   3 pounds hamburger
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons salt
</P>
<P>
   1 onion, chopped very fine
</P>
<P>
   4 cups Del Monte ketchup
</P>
<P>
   2-ounce bottle Mexene chili powder
</P>
<P>
   1 cup water
</P>
<P>
   Place all ingredients in large saucepan. Mix well. Bring to a
boil, then simmer for 1 hour. Make sure to stir often to keep sauce
from burning or scorching.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 324 calories, 15 grams fat, 22
grams carbohydrates, 25 grams protein, 86 milligrams cholesterol,
1,439 milligrams sodium, 38 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   LA MADELEINE'S STRAWBERRIES ROMANOFF
</P>
<P>
   Serves 2
</P>
<P>
   1 cup strawberries, hulled and rinsed
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup sour cream
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons brown sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon brandy
</P>
<P>
   Just before serving, rinse berries and trim stems with a paring
knife. Mix remaining ingredients and let stand for 2 to 3 minutes.
Put berries in stemmed wine glass and top with sauce.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 370 calories, 25 grams fat, 30
grams carbohydrates, 4 grams protein, 52 milligrams cholesterol, 69
milligrams sodium, 60 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
