of the Coyote Cafes in Santa Fe and Las Vegas and Red Sage in
Washington, D.C., knew he wanted a kitchen where he could entertain
and work without the noise, activity and interruptions of his
restaurant kitchens. But he also wanted the functional advantages
of professional equipment. And a place to play. By BEVERLY BUNDY.
