   FINANCIAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   TIRE-RECALL (Washington) _ Bridgestone/Firestone said Wednesday
the treads on millions of tires it has produced since 1991 seem
unusually prone to fly off the tire bodies for reasons it cannot
yet explain, sometimes with catastrophic results. And facing 50
lawsuits, 46 deaths, 80 injuries and a federal safety
investigation, the company said that it would provide free
replacements for the 6.5 million tires still on the road. By
Matthew L. Wald.
</P>
<P>
   LILLY-PROZAC (Undated) _ A federal appeals court reversed a
lower court's decision that gave Prozac patent protection through
2003. Eli Lilly, which makes Prozac, says the ruling may clear the
way for Barr Laboratories to put a generic version of Prozac on the
market in a year. Prozac accounts for 26 percent of Lilly's sales.
Lilly says it will appeal. By Melody Petersen.
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-CONJOINED-TWINS (Undated) _ In a surgical tour de force,
performed with minutes to spare, doctors in Boston separated
conjoined twins who shared a heart. Because of highly unusual
circulatory abnormalities, one of the twins was doomed; the
question was, could the other be saved? Through elaborate planning,
including computer modeling, the doctors found a way to save her
and now, at 14 months, she is living with her family in Paterson,
N.J., and doing well. By Denise Grady. (1600 words)
</P>
