<HEADER>
A6924 &Cx1f; tad-z
r l BC-GARDENING-LIFE10-COX     08-09 0078
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GARDENING-LIFE10-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Life and gardening go on despite fall of massive tree
 &HT;    By Lee May
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   After my July 27 column about the old oak from next door
crushing my garden with one of its two trunks, many readers wrote
with condolences, reminiscences _ and humor, which so often helps
mitigate pain. The e-mail:
</P>
<P>
   Elizabeth and Courtney
</P>
<P>
   Siceloff of Atlanta:
</P>
<P>
   (We've) just read of the fallen oak, and want to extend
condolenc
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-09-00 1650EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT20000809.0191 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-09 16:50 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6925 &Cx1f; tab-z
