<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-09 17:58 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6975 &Cx1f; tad-z
u f BC-BEllSOUTH-WIRELESS081     08-09 0297
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BEllSOUTH-WIRELESS0810-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    BellSouth wireless data unit gets new CEO
 &HT;    By Michael E. Kanell
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA - BellSouth has named Don Kovalevich president and chief
executive of its wireless data unit.
</P>
<P>
   Kovalevich, who has been president and general manager of
Houston Cellular Telephone Co., said he has seen demand for
wireless phones explode in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
   ``Wireless data is similarly positioned today,'' he said.
``People want data available anytime, anywhere, and the technology
is here to support that.''
</P>
<P>
   BellSouth's wireless data unit, based in New Jersey, sells a
two-messaging service on pagers made by RIM Technologies. The
company's national wireless network is also used by the newest
generation of Palm personal digital assistants.
</P>
<P>
   Although data and Internet capabilities are increasingly
available on wireless phones, Kovalevich said he expects them to
serve a somewhat different audience than that of the pagers.
``These are different markets with different needs.''
</P>
<P>
   Phones have to combine a host of features in one device and thus
far are limited in the speed with which they transmit data. That
makes them more suited for the ``casual'' data user, he said.
</P>
<P>
   The wireless data unit will be part of the new company being
created by combining the wireless businesses of BellSouth and SBC
Communications. While SBC's wireless phone business is larger than
BellSouth's, SBC has no similar data unit.
</P>
<P>
   William Lenahan resigned as president in May. With appointment
of Kovalevich, J.D. Gardner, who had served as acting president and
CEO since then, will return to his job as the unit's chief
financial officer.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-09-00 1758EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
