drive tied to the convention in Los Angeles. By Don Van Natta Jr.
and John M. Broder.
</P>
<P>
   TIRE-RECALL (Washington) _ Bridgestone/Firestone, a subsidiary
of Japan's Bridgestone Corp., said Wednesday the treads on millions
of tires it has produced since 1991 seem unusually prone to fly off
the tire bodies for reasons it cannot yet explain, sometimes with
catastrophic results. And facing 50 lawsuits, 46 deaths, 80
injuries and a federal safety investigation, the company said that
it would provide free replacements. By Matthew L. Wald.
</P>
