<P>
   SOUTHERN-TOBACCO _ LEXINGTON, Ky. _ Southern tobacco farmers are
nervous. Growers in Kentucky, North Carolina, Georgia, Tennessee
and South Carolina farm 90 percent of the domestic crop. But a $145
billion anti-tobacco verdict in Florida has many wondering whether
this is the straw that's broken Joe Camel's back. Will they turn to
catfish farms and grape vineyards or car sales? We check and see.
Pegged to meeting of big tobacco on Aug. 14. (Manuel, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
