</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) NEW YORK -- Aug. 9, 2000 -- CANDIDATES-SONGS -- Before
soft money and sound bites and spin doctors and tightly scripted
conventions, presidential candidates were something to sing about.
Oscar Brand, who is better known as a radio personality and protege
of folk song stars like Woody Guthrie and Pete Seeger, is still
singing about presidential candidates of the past. Brand in his
Manhattan home on Tuesday. (Nicole Bengiveno/The New York Times)
</P>
