<HEADLINE>
RATINGS UPGRADE BOOSTS VITESSE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROBERT MONROE 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   CAMARILLO, Calif. _ Shares of Vitesse Semiconductor jumped 15.3
percent Wednesday to close at $70.31 after a Banc of America
analyst upgraded its rating from ``buy'' to ``strong buy.''
</P>
<P>
   Analyst Alex Gauna said in a report that the company will
experience accelerated growth from sales to clients Fujitsu and
Lucent Technologies.
</P>
<P>
   He added that he is elevating his earnings estimate to 20 cents
from 19 cents a share for the fourth quarter. He also predicts
strong profits across the entire broadband semiconductor industry.
</P>
<P>
   Shares of Vitesse rose $9.38 on heavy trading of 10.5 million
shares.
</P>
<P>
   The company declined to comment on the stock's performance.
</P>
<P>
   Vitesse makes digital chips called gallium arsenide integrated
circuits that are faster than silicon. The chips are used in
Internet and optical network settings.
</P>
<P>
   Analyst Aalok Shah of Pacific Crest Securities said the stock
has long been undervalued. Vitesse's performance Wednesday had as
much to do with the strong performance of its major clients, Cisco
Systems, as with its own upgrade.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been a great stock. The company is doing everything they
said they'd do,'' Shah said. ``You're going to see the stock go
even higher than it is now.''
</P>
